Troubleshooting
For the Flow to be triggered, the Snowflake B2B2C_Promo_Decoupling task needs to be first executed. If the Flow is not executed when it should be (approx 11:30am each Thursday) then first step is to check if Snowflake task was fully executed.

Errors within the Flow itself, will likely come from altering any file or folder that is referenced within the Flow. As there are a number of files to be created (x2 SAP journals, x3 supporting files and n* x SSD files) a .txt file has been created, b2b2c-transaction-files/Output Files/Promo_Decoupling_Master_Folder_Names.txt, to store the relevant folder pairs between Azure Blob Storage and Sharepoint:



{
  "Data": [
    {
      "Blob_Name": "AP_Journal",
      "Sharepoint_Name": "AP Journals"
    },
    {
      "Blob_Name": "AP_Supporting_Doc",
      "Sharepoint_Name": "AP Supporting Document"
    },
    {
      "Blob_Name": "Debit_Note_Extract",
      "Sharepoint_Name": "Debit Note Macro Data"
    },
   {
      "Blob_Name": "GL_Extract",
      "Sharepoint_Name": "GL Extract by Store"
    },
   {
      "Blob_Name": "GL_Journal",
      "Sharepoint_Name": "GL Journals"
    }
  ]
}
In the above .txt file, “Blob_Name” refers to folders stored in b2b2c-transaction-files/Output Files within our Azure Blob Storage, and “Sharepoint_Name” refers to folders stored in B2B2C Supplier Reports - B2B2C Data Extracts. 
